Introduction
The associations between sleep and attention-
deﬁcit hyperactivity disorders (ADHD) have been a
focus for clinical and empirical efforts over the last
two decades. A number of narrative literature
reviews addressed this issue in recent years.1–5
These reviews conveyed the

